Turkcell, Yapi & Kredi Bankasi: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-04-26T06:34:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-26/turkcell-yapi-kredi-bankasi-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in  Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  rose 178.90, or
0.3 percent, to 68,870.67 yesterday.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): The executive
board of Turkey’s biggest mobile-phone operator will meet
tomorrow to discuss when to hold an extraordinary meeting of
shareholders, Haberturk newspaper reported. Shareholders Altimo
and TeliaSonera AB last week blocked dividend payments and the
approval of Turkcell’s 2010 balance sheet when chairman Colin
Williams declined to discuss changes to the board and government
officials backed him. Turkcell fell 22 kurus, or 2.4 percent, to
8.96 liras.  Yapi & Kredi Bankasi AS (YKBNK TI): The Turkish bank part-
owned by UniCredit SpA applied to the market regulator to offer
3.2 billion liras ($2.1 billion) of bonds to investors and plans
to sell another 300 million liras of bonds via private
placement, the bank said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange  after the market closed yesterday. Yapi Kredi gained 2
kurus, or 0.4 percent, to 4.77 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
